<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bowl1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bowl,</orth> subst., 1) a vessel to drink in, rather wide than deep: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.935" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 935</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 63</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.4.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 4, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 142</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.184" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 184</bibl>. <cit><quote>a gossip's b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 47</bibl></cit>.*<bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 175</bibl>. <emph>standing b.</emph> (i. e. a bowl resting on a foot) <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 3, 65</bibl>; cf. Stage-direction in <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5</bibl>.<lb />2) ball of wood used for play: <bibl n="shak. cor 5.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 1, 8</bibl>. <cit><quote>thus the b. should run,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.5.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 5, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>at --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 4, 3</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 1, 54</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>